<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd2cbd0fb-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s1402"><num value="1402">§ 1402.</num><heading> Rule of construction</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each range of frequencies described in this chapter shall be construed to be inclusive of the upper and lower frequencies in the range.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd2cbd0fc-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">(<ref href="/us/pl/112/96/tVI/s6002">Pub. L. 112–96, title VI, § 6002</ref>, <date date="2012-02-22">Feb. 22, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/204">126 Stat. 204</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
